            to Hacker

        h3.deck An ongoing journey

        hr

        p.
          About six months ago, as of this writing, I knew only enough HTML and CSS
          to rearrange a website. I've come a long way since.

        p.
          A year out from being laid off from a job in the thriving world of
          print journalism, I've taken a detour back to another interest of mine—technology.
          I've set out on a mission to learn to code, to create clean, logical websites and apps,
          and to learn the correct way to accomplish these tasks. Halfway through the Nashville Software
          School program, I'm well on my way to that goal but with the knowledge that
          I'll never be done learning.

        p.
          Here are many of the concepts, applications and frameworks that I've been exposed
          to so far in two and a half months:
        hr
        .row#list
          .col-md-4
            ul.list
              li HTML
              li CSS
